During a press briefing, Karine Jean-Pierre, the White House Deputy Press Secretary, announced that the President and First Lady will be traveling to Hawaii on Monday to meet with first responders, survivors, and officials in response to the devastating fires in Maui. The briefing also featured FEMA Administrator Deanne Criswell, who provided updates on the ongoing recovery efforts in Hawaii. Criswell highlighted the support provided by federal agencies and emphasized the long and difficult road to recovery ahead. The briefing also touched on the one-year anniversary of the Inflation Reduction Act, with Senior Advisor John Podesta and Domestic Policy Advisor Neera Tanden discussing the transformative impact of the legislation. They highlighted the investments in clean energy and climate action, as well as the benefits for healthcare and reducing prescription drug costs. They also addressed concerns about the cost of the legislation and emphasized the positive economic impact and job creation resulting from the investments.